title: For Sale/Trade:  Non Refurbished Mosin Nagant (Izy, 1939)
postcontent:
Up for your viewing is a nonrefurbished mosin!
Since I can only upload one picture, please pardon me and email for more; I will get to you after my classes.
 
It has an import stamp on barrel by the cleaning rod, and has matching serials on receiver and barrel.
Bolt is an 1891 type, with a reserialzed handle and nonmatching serialized cocking nob.
The floorplate is tight fitting and also a different serial.
Buttplate is also of the same catigory - mismatched but pre WW2.
The stock and recevier are not marked with any known rearsenal marks.
Stock has the round soviet mark on every 91/30 izhevesk, but is also circle-MA marked and overall has battle gouges and scratches, errr, character.
The barrel is counterbored, the rifling is very good compared to my other mosins, and the bolt had yet to be cleaned of cosmoline when I bought it.
 
It is my theory that the bolt, magazine, and buttplate were either battlefeild replacements or salvaged from the Winter War in 1939 for reuse in new production 91/30s.
How it got counterbored without a rearsenalling is unknow to me, unless either it isn't truely nonrefurbished or counterboring was done in the feild or in the war.
If you have further knowledge about this rifle, or desire pictures, do not hesitate to contact me.
Thank you for your time, (and hope the text isn't a jumbled mess)!
